+
+What makes it realistic: the silhouette follows the actual profile curve (125 m base tapering to the summit at ~300 m, antenna to 330 m), the four legs stand as independent lattice pylons that merge at the first floor, and the body is a genuine cross-braced iron lattice ÔÇö thousands of X-braced panels, denser below the second floor just like the real structure. It includes the decorative double-ring arches under the first platform, all three platforms with railings at their correct heights (57 m, 115 m, 276 m), the summit cabin and broadcast mast, and the paint is graduated in three shades of "Eiffel Tower brown," darker at the base and lighter at the top, as the real tower is painted.
+
+Drag to orbit, scroll or pinch to zoom, and it slowly rotates when idle. Toggle to Night mode for the golden illumination with the twinkling white sparkle effect from the hourly light show.
